Post title: cmi.core.lesson_status on second entry to sco
Post description: Hi All, I'm authoring a 3-sco scorm 1.2 package using Flash CS3. I'm only setting one cmi.core value, cmi.core.lesson_status. I set it to "incomplete" when the first frame of the swf loads, and to "completed" when the last frame of the swf loads. I'm doing this by importing flash.external.ExternalInterface into Flash, importing APIWrapper.js (from ADL) into the HTML page which contains the swf embed. The setting of the values works great. If I enter a sco, then leave it, lesson_status is set to "incomplete". If I go all the way to the end, lesson_status is set to "completed". The problem is that every time I enter the sco, the old value is erased by the new. So if I've completed the sco already, and I enter and do not finish it a second time, the sco lesson_status is reset to "incomplete"! I've looked at the scoring settings for the Moodle scorm activity, and changed them around quite a bit, and it doesn't seem to make any difference. Perhaps what's needed is a revision to the function in APIWrapper.js so that it only changes lesson_status to "incomplete" if it isn't already set. I'll see if I can write some JS to make that happen. But if anyone out there has already had to think through this, or has any bright ideas, I'd sure appreciate suggestions. Humbly, Amy
Comments associated with the post: 
Comment 1: Hi... I used flash as my platform to develop sco. I set my publish setting to SCORM 1.2. This will generate the API scripts inside the html file. By default the completion status is "incomplete" To make my sco completed, i've pass the completion status as "completed" at the end of page/sco. It works. Eventhough i browse the sco many times, the status still "completed" , if i've completed the sco at the first time. Regards
Comment 2: i recommend you write your own logic in the swf at the first frame or a function in the js file since we also have had to cope with this.  the lesson status can be controlled at any point as you have found out (there is separate rule for SCO with exam where LMS decides on passed/failed by referring to manifest score val) so we have had to program the initial check along the lines "get lesson_Status and if lesson_status does not equal "completed" then lesson_status = "incomplete" "  just do not let your first screen overwrite "completed".
Comment 3: Clear as a bell. Get, if != "completed", Set. Thanks. Glad to know I wasn't the only one. A
Comment 4: Boo-yeah! Got it working. Here's my code, in case anyone else might benefit: 
```text




import flash.external.ExternalInterface;











// function to get cmi values using APIWrapper.js







function GetValue(n:String):String {



	var R:String;



	var doGetValue = ExternalInterface.call("doLMSGetValue", n);



	R = String(doGetValue);



	return (R);



}











// function to set cmi values using APIWrapper.js







function SetValue(n:String, v:String):Void {



	var doSetValue = ExternalInterface.call("doLMSSetValue", n, v);



}







// function to check lesson status and set to incomplete if 



// it's not already set to "completed"







function setIfNotCompleted() {



	var x:String = "cmi.core.lesson_status";



	var lessonStatus:String = null;



	lessonStatus = GetValue(x);



	if (lessonStatus != "completed") {



		SetValue("cmi.core.lesson_status","incomplete");



		ExternalInterface.call("doLMSCommit");



	}



}







// call conditional function to set status to incomplete







setIfNotCompleted();
```
Comment 5: Hi Amy, Could you please tell me in which file should we include this code ? Regards
Comment 6: Hi. This code goes right in your Flash file. I usually create a layer called "actions," and this code goes on a keyframe on the first screen of the actions layer, on the first screen of the movie. So that as soon as it loads, status is set (if not previously set), to "incomplete". You also need to call the SetValue function to set status to "completed". 
```text




SetValue("cmi.core.lesson_status","completed");



ExternalInterface.call("doLMSCommit");
```
 You will call this function in the actions layer on the last page of the movie. So if you have a SCORM package with 3 scos, and each sco is a .fla for which you want to track lesson_status, you will have to add these functions to every single .fla, at the beginning of the movie, and call the GetValue and SetValue functions accordingly. Hope that makes sense. The project is proprietary, so I can't share it, but I might be able to create a rough template, given time. Good luck, Amy
